items.text: Ah-maziiiing!
Had the premium Chirashi Don: when you charge $50 & call it premium, I don't think you should be serving run-of-the-mill maguro. Overall only an average experience but may return to try other items
Almost everything! Sake, sushi, sashimi
The chirashi is top notch. A worthy Teppei alternative any time.
Really thick sashimi slices. Doesn't add up to be that cheap though.
Basically you can't go wrong with anything here, except wait times should you choose to do a walk-in. Be sure to reserve a week or more in advance to avoid disappointment. you can SMS 96536464.
Salmon omnomnomburi is amazing
Value4$ - sashimi slices were thick. Super love the salmon fin nitsuke which is on promo now @ $12.90 and was recommended by waitress. Fish miso soup also on promo 1-for-1 at $4.90. Cash or nets.
Very expensive with GST and Service Charge (where service sucks). Not worth it. Might as well go for some classy Japanese restaurant instead. $25 for 2 plates of simple sushi is a no-go.
Slow service = long queue
Be prepared to cue. Scallops mentaiyaki are popular for a reason. Could do with better service.
cash only!
Drinking water? Help yourself. Hot water to refill ur green tea? Self service. Done w ur meal? Take ur order clipboard to the cashier & pay (cash only, no NETS, no credit cards)
Strangely they don't sell Inari sushi
First experience and likely my last 😩 I Guess u already know my comments 😰
Food is definitely very fresh and nice. But service is not very welcoming.
$4.90 per FRESH oyster!! 😍 Smooth Oyster Shot!!
The normal chirashi is generous with the fish - thick slices of hamachi, salmon, tuna, swordfish... But rice portion not as filling
The 100g of sirloin steak... It comes medium rare... Another so-so dish for me!! Maybe it was suppose to resemble sashimi - had a similar texture 😊
Really goof food at affordable pricing～
Their Chirashi don is awesome!

Chirashi here are as excellent as what everyone positively reviewed w thick sashimi slices. Dried puffer fish tastes really delicious like a much better version of our grilled cuttlefish #ThomtoriEats
Love the Chirashi here!! Go at 2pm for no Q but it closes at 3pm and there is NETS payment 😝
chirashi don wasn't fresh, overpriced at $25. softshell crab salmon aburi maki was decent but also not really worth $17
Super good sirloin steak.salmon agubi roll is a MUST try!
Fresh sashimi and love the sushi here. Come early to avoid the long queue.
Order the salmon aburi roll! 👍
Had the normal charashi Don with chawamushi and weekday special spicy sashimi sides. Overall quite good, would come back again.  Nice staffs, keep up the good service.
Chawanmushi is super smooth! Must try!
Wafu Spaghetti!!! $10.90... Very creamy and have good flavour if u like the Mentayaki taste... Good for sharing not to be eaten on its own!!
The soft shell Crab appetiser was rather greasy and the sauce didn't cut the grease well. Ebi fry handroll was also rather greasy
The fresh seafood is very good here. Quite a random hole in the wall but you won't be disappointed.
Scallop Mentayaki... Although it's a chef recommendation... It was so-so for me!! But I did like the charred-bits!
The queue is always crazy. Usually the wait is 45 minutes. Salmon aburi roll and chirashi don make it worth the wait. they've started charging gst and service charge though, no credit cards accepted!
Mentai items and sashimi . Could improve on unagi though
Spicy Salmon Maki ... Not so pretty... But son had no complaints!!
You can avoid the queue by coming later at ard 1.30pm.
Chirashi... Asked for one without tuna!! Wah the sashimi all were thickly cut 👍 on a thin bed of rice!
Nice sushi. Still warm like it's just been made. Reasonable price. Recommended.
I'm astounded by the amount of comments on service. This place is all about the food. Go elsewhere if you want service. Awesome sushi. Very fresh, authentic and worth the wait. Cash only.
Chirashi don (whatever they have. the seasonal ones are legendary), the Soft Shell Crab Aburi Roll and the Ebi Fry Aburi Roll.
Worth the wait
For reservations on weekdays, SMS to 96536464. They don't take reservations for weekends, eve of public holidays, & public holidays. Source: Company FB page
Super thick salmon sashimi for only SGD$4.90! Service was quite alight unlike the most comments here. Definitely coming back again! 🍣🍣
amazing food; though quality is slipping every time I come back. the first time I tried Sushi Bar a year half ago was mindblowing!
The service is veryyyyyyyy slowwwwwwwwww
Just order the Chirashi don. It won't disappoint.
go after 8pm less queue.
Queue before it's even open!
Salmon aburi sushi roll is a must try!
Normal chirashi-don @ $25++ looks decent and are sliced thickly, BUT all my swordfish had sinews in it! Eeeeeks!!
Tip: Great deals on Asahi Beer 3x $20nett
The place opens 12:30pm for lunch (Mon-Sat). Come early or else u get this long a queue. Small place. Seating for only 48 people
Good food!
Bad service. Was given wrong order but staff insisted it was what we agreed to. Overly hyped place

Came in first thing they said "you have to leave by 6.45pm." Sat down ordering, they didn't have sushi. Then no salmon skin no this n that. Then we had I wait 20 min for our food when we only had 1hr.
Chawanmushi is a small serving but smooth and yummy!!
Food was not bad, but I was surprised by the prices. Felt rather overpriced considering items, ambience, and location...
Very satisfying!!
Very value for money food. Must try the pitan tofu and soft shell crab roll. Thick slices of fish with minimal rice. Recommended!
Sea food super fresh !
What restaurant opens at 1230 and don't let customers sit in the meantime when all the prep work is behind the counter???
If you are going in pairs... They would squeeze you on the same table with strangers😢. Just my luck I was seated next to a self-righteous chap who "knew everything"!! There's NETS payment by the way!
Chirashi don was good!
Enjoyed our sushi (salmon, hamachi, hotate, sake, sake aburi). Coming back for more. The right amt of rice (not too much) supporting the main prized fish meat above :-)
Pitan tofu is everything
Sushi! Yep
Pretty good sushi and chirashi don. But a bit more expensive than I expected.
